{"questionId":"9067409","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The equations show steps in the formation and decomposition of ozone in the stratosphere, some of which absorb ultraviolet light.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><br>Step 1&nbsp; &nbsp; O<sub>2</sub> → 2O•</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Step 2&nbsp; &nbsp; O• + O<sub>2</sub> → O<sub>3</sub></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Step 3&nbsp; &nbsp; O<sub>3</sub> → O• + O<sub>2</sub></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Step 4&nbsp; &nbsp; O• + O<sub>3</sub> → 2O<sub>2</sub></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Identify the steps which absorb ultraviolet light.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">steps 1 <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>3 ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067409","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.e(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify the steps which absorb ultraviolet light.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure","14.1 Covalent bonding and electron domain and molecular geometries","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}